            <p>Kingston Jamaica 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Ocbr 5622<lb/>
                The Revrd Morais<lb/>
                Revrd Sir.<lb/></p>
            <p>Pardon me for trespassing on your<lb/> time&#44; but having seen your valued letters in reply to<lb/> the Revrd. Mr DeSola&#39;s Pamphlet&#44; which shows the<lb/> deep interest you take in our religious matters&#44; I am<lb/> led to hope you will not think me intrusive by<lb/> asking for your <sic>opininion</sic> on a question that<lb/> has created much unhappy discussion here.<lb/></p>
            <p>I am Revrd Sir personally known to the<lb/> Revrd Isaac Leeser and he I am sure will be happy<lb/> to satisfy you of the character of the writer who now<lb/> claims your earnest attention.<lb/></p>
            <p>I beg to enclose you copy of a letter I have<lb/> addressed to the Revrd Dr. Raphael which as it contains<lb/> the full merits of the question in dispute&#44; will serve<lb/> equally to afford you the information I desire<lb/> to convey.  If you Revrd Sir will favor me with<lb/> a reply <hi rend="underline">thro&#39; the Occident</hi> where the subject will be<lb/> fully ventilated by the several Gentlemen to whom<lb/> I had written&#44; you will place me under deep obligation.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have written to my friend Mr. Leeser to<lb/> request the use of his columns so that the&#45;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>so that the publication of my letter to Dr. Raphael<lb/> will form the ground upon which the several<lb/> replies and opinions will be given<lb/></p>
            <p>I have the honor to remain<lb/>
                Revrd Sir<lb/>
                Yours most respectfully<lb/>
                M M Sollas<lb/>
            </p>
            
        </body>
    </text>
